<br>
Not sure if this belongs here, but since I am somewhat of a newbie when it comes to macros, I thought why not.<br>
<br>
I hear people say bind FD to a movement key, it will go up fast.<br>
<br>
How is this done?<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
Rabshale <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=glaydor>Glaydor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.mustangworks.com/gatorstang23/alig.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/8/02 1:01:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1682.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Macros</span><hr size=1> first go to your abilities key and see what ability number it is<br>
1 2<br>
3 4<br>
5 6<br>
<br>
<br>
Then go to your socials key and make a macro like this<br>
<br>
Named: FDprac<br>
/doability &lt;number that fd is&gt;<br>
/sit off<br>
<br>
<br>
Thats it. I didnt put this into a movement key. I just clicked the button while running or just standing around. the sit off makes it so you dont have to hit the sit key to stand up <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220310</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueleyrin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eleyrin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/8/02 1:39:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1682.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Macros</span><hr size=1> binding FD to a movement key would be annoying, as you would ALWAYS flop the ground every 10 seconds when you are moving, and you would have to manually hit stand. Glaydor's method is best for FD.<br>
<br>
However, for other skills (senseheading, forage, some clicky effects on higher level items come to mind), you can set an inventory button to the senseheading hotkey. Then in your keymappings, you can remap &quot;Hotbox 1&quot; (or similar, I forget the exact text) from &quot;1&quot;, to &quot;left arrow&quot;. From now on, whenever you hit your left arrow key, it will press sense heading for you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaitanniyan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daitan Niyan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/14/02 7:23:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1682.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Macros</span><hr size=1> Here's what i did, which is similar to what Glaydor has:<br>
<br>
/doability x (x=Sense Heading)<br>
/doability y (y=Instill Doubt)<br>
/doability z (z=Fiegn Death)<br>
/sit            (no need to add &quot;off&quot; /sit will stand you up)<br>
<br>
Then, drag the social to a hotkey button. As i Level, I spam this hotkey in offtime, running, waiting for Nexus Ports, Boat rides, etc. For Instill Doubt to work, you must have something targetted. I.E. a Mob, an NPC, another Player, whatever, just be careful to stay out of melee range if it's a mob/NPC you don't want to fight. A successful ID will result in a kick, which, if it lands, fears the mob (resistable). This can result in some unpleasantness if for example say, you have the Nexus Scion targetted, and Your ID succeeds. (the one in Gfay Punches for a solid 1300+ BTW) Good luck, <br>
<br>
Regards, <p><b><i>Daitan Niyan</b></i>
